      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection of papers of Bertha Gray Robinson consists
         of 300 items. Editorial papers of Robinson include
         correspondence regarding the 
         <title render="italic">Orange Observer</title>, 1880-1936, and
         subscription accounts, addresses, and lists. Family
         correspondence of John Jones Robinson and sons, James A.
         Robinson and Robert Newton Robinson, convey family news and
         frequently mention the 
         <title render="italic">Orange Observer</title>as well as the
         Oxford, N.C., 
         <title render="italic">Torch-light</title>and the Winston,
         N.C., 
         <title render="italic">Leader.</title>The collection also
         contains penmanship copybooks, photographs, greeting cards,
         advertisements and miscellaneous printed material.</p>
      </scopecontent>
